    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "innovation? i'm just running a local hardware store, i can't exactly \"innovate\" my way out of needing to pay my guy $3 more an hour. it feels like you're saying the struggle of actually managing the books is just a \"healthy sign\" of something. is there really no downside at all if i'm stuck between raising prices on my neighbors or just cutting staff? isn't that a legit concern for a real business owner?",
